author: timesunion.com
title: Rodger's Quick Take
text: The Jets won't upset the Patriots on Sunday in Foxborough, Mass., but they can make it interesting. The Jets have the top-ranked rushing offense while the Patriots' defense is ranked 22nd against the run. The Jets have one of the better defenses in the NFL and they will bring the pressure on quarterback Tom Brady Nobody handles pressure better than Brady, but remember, the Jets' secondary is led by a former Patriots DB, Darrelle Revis , who is considered one of best cover guys in the NFL. The Patriots will improve to 6-0, but the Jets will keep it close, start to finish. NewsChannel 13's Rodger Wyland can be heard weekdays from 9 a.m. to noon on WOFX 980 AM.
